Installation

	Before driver installation. Make sure system with gcc compiler and
	kernel development package.

	Driver install
		Create a temp directory
		$ cd ~
		$ mkdir temp

		After get driver package file. Copy file to ~/temp directory,
		then extract and install.

		$ cp DRIVER_PACKAGE.tar.zip ~/temp 
		$ cd ~/temp
		$ tar xvf DRIVER_PACKAGE.tar.zip
		Apply the patch if needed, describe in README_Distribution
		$ patch -p1 < ../patch/PATCHFILE

		$ make
		$ sudo make install

	Driver uninstall
		Close all driver device node (/dev/sdc_dio0, /dev/ttyS4 ..etc)
		$ cd ~/temp/DRIVER_PACKAGE/driver
		$ sudo make uninstall
	
	GPIO support
		If the DIO controller needs to work with the Linux GPIO
		subsystem instead of the char device (SUNIX Library API),
		change the make command
		$ make FSDC_ENABLE_GPIO=1

